<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,258,571]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,476,366,391]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Differential Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from other members of the group by the comparatively large mesoventral plaques, each of which is larger than the area separating them. Otherwise, the habitus is very similar to that of 
<emphasis box="[235,438,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2017" box="[235,435,438,463]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ambohitantely">H. ambohitantely</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The aedeagi of the two species are quite dissimilar; that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2017" box="[1134,1269,439,462]" class="Insecta" family="Hydraenidae" genus="Hydraena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marojejy">
<emphasis box="[1134,1269,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">H. marojejy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
notable in the large (in lateral view) flattened distal lobe that narrows to form a pick-like process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,258,571]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
